Title: Local modes, local vacuum, local bogoljubov coefficients and the

renormalised stress tensorAuthors: S. Massar

Comments: (talk presented at Journees relativistes 93), 4 pages (LATEX),ULB-TH

09/93Journal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. D3 (1994) 237-240

Local modes and local particles are defined at any point in curved space timeas those that most resemble Minkowsky modes at that point. It is shown that therenormalised stress tensor is the difference of energy between the physicalvacuum and that defined by these local modes.